news.title: Single-family housing starts in US drop 14.2% to 940,000 units in March
news.para: President Donald Trump has slapped import duties on virtually all foreign goods and his trade policy has been rapidly shifting, raising fears of inflation re-igniting and dimming the economy's outlook.

news.title: Aurika Residences to invest Rs 100 crore to build hospitality project in Ayodhya
news.para: Chauhan said the company will fund this investment through internal accruals and bank loans. Noida-based Aurika Group is into housing, commercial and hospitality segments.

news.title: Goa CM signals support to regularise unauthorised homes in Margao
news.para: ​​The chief minister added that his govt would “take an appropriate decision on regularisation of houses,” signalling potential govt action to legitimise these structures.

news.title: Panchayat raj department gives nod to industrial parks in Telangana villages
news.para: IADA will manage key aspects of the project, including land acquisition, road construction, and other infrastructural developments required for setting up the industrial units.

news.title: Conscient Infrastructure to invest ₹1,200 crore to develop residential project in Gurugram
news.para: The company is targeting a topline of over ₹1,000 crore through the sale of 268 luxury apartments in the first phase. Apartment's price will start at 14,500 per sq ft.

news.title: Cement prices likely to improve on strong demand: Nuvama Research
news.para: In April 2025, cement prices have risen across all regions, with the southern region leading the surge, followed by the eastern, central, northern and western parts of the country.

news.title: REITs to drive institutional investment in India's office spaces: Nuvama Report
news.para: The report underscores the cautious private equity (PE) investments during the period 2022 and 2023 due to the concerns over rising inflation and interest rates.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body reclaims 11 shops near Keshavrao Bhosale Natyagruha for redevelopment
news.para: The Kolhapur Municipal Corporation (KMC) reclaimed the shops in the presence of a heavy police force on Tuesday. As KMC needed public utility space in the reconstruction of the Natyagruha, notices were served to the tenants.

news.title: Building permits for apartments in Germany fall 2.3% in February
news.para: Germany's property sector, which began to shrink in 2022, is undergoing its most severe slump in decades. Permits are an important indicator of future construction activity.

news.title: EPR framework to tackle C&D waste in India from April 26
news.para: The construction sector, expected to hit $1.4 tn by 2025, will be the biggest economic growth and debris source. As housing, industrial corridors and road networks expand, so, too, will the waste load. NCR generates 6,303 tonnes of C&D waste a day.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government forms panel to probe charges against Ansal group
news.para: The nine-member committee, to be headed by Lucknow's divisional commissioner, will go through a five-point agenda set forth by the govt.

news.title: MDDA assures Uttarakhand HC of demolition against unauthorised constructions in Rishikesh
news.para: The bench was hearing a petition filed by Rishikesh residents, including Pankaj Agarwal, alleging that unauthorised constructions were being carried out in the city's housing development area in violation of sanctioned plans.

news.title: Higher rentals to fuel demand for property purchases in 2025
news.para: The year 2025 is likely to witness an increase in property purchases with the rapid appreciation in prices in the rental market which is even outpacing capital growth in multiple regions.

news.title: Jaipur: SC denies interim relief to Aravalli miners
news.para: A bench of Justice B R Gavai and Justice K V Viswanathan refused to entertain the plea for interim relief and issued a warning against such speculative and repetitive applications.

news.title: Goa HC orders compliance reports on illegal constructions by June 12
news.para: The HC adjourned the case to June 13. “As far as compliances are concerned, the HC has granted municipalities and panchayats until June 12 to comply with its order,” advocate general Devidas Pangam told reporters after the hearing.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body to call up top 100 property taxpayers to boost collection
news.para: The tax branch staff, responsible for property tax matters, will reach out to these high-value taxpayers to ensure they submit their payments during the current rebate period.

news.title: Noida: YEIDA to issue reservation letter for 7% abadi plots to farmers
news.para: A verification committee comprising the deputy collector, project manager, law officer, the concerned OSD, and the tehsildar will be constituted to ensure timely scrutiny and finalisation of the allotments.

news.title: Net leasing of office space rises 54% to 127.8 lakh sq ft across seven major cities in Q4 FY25: JLL
news.para: Gross leasing of office space increased 28 per cent in January-March this year at 19.46 million (194.6 lakh) square feet, the highest among all previous first quarters of any calendar year.

news.title: Noida: GNIDA recommends suspension of six officials for irregularities in plot allotment
news.para: In 2023, a scheme for residential plots, spanning 9,660 square metres, was launched by the Greater Noida Authority at Patwari village in Sector 2.

news.title: Prime minister to relaunch Amaravati construction work on May 2
news.para: "Prime Minister Narendra Modi is coming on May 2 to relaunch Amaravati construction works and in this regard all arrangements are being made," said the Chief Secretary in an official release.
